  "prompt": "Why didn't Jennifer Hudson speak at the Republican Convention in support of Donald Trump?",
  "response": "Jennifer Hudson, along with her legal representatives, requested the Trump campaign to cease using her performance of \"Hallelujah\" at a December 2019 memorial service for victims of gun violence at the 2020 Republican National Convention. They emphasized that this request was not based on politics but rather aligned with the mission of the foundation she established in memory of her mother, brother, and nephew, who were lost to gun violence.\n\nHudson\u2019s foundation is dedicated to aiding families affected by such tragedies. The use of her performance at the memorial service, which was a poignant and non-political event, at a political convention was deemed inappropriate and contradictory to the foundation's mission. As a result, this incident, rather than her personal political stance, served as the public reason for her not participating in speaking at the Republican National Convention in support of Donald Trump. It\u2019s important to note that this situation highlights the broader issue of the what and when of using artists' work in political contexts, rather than indicating Jennifer Hudson\u2019s direct involvement or political affiliations.",
